{
  "texts": [
    "Results are reported aggregated in Table 1.",
    "Larger models attain lower errors, though Qwen-7B and G1-7B perform comparably on Easy and Medium tasks.",
    "G1-7B surpasses Qwen on only 7 /12 tasks, thus no \"universal winner\" emerges (App. fig.",
    "While fine-tuning with G1-7B improves sMAPE on harder problems (e.g., eigenvector_centrality, heat_trace, fig. 11), on these tasks it remains not better than the mean baseline, as RelMAE is larger than 1.0.",
    "Overall, we observe G1-7B outperforms this in 50% of the tasks, but the gains are still limited (RelMAE in [0.6, 0.9])."
  ]
}